																		Author Post
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/techsorcerer2747" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2921100); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2921100&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610249918" alt="TechSorcerer2747" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2921100)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/techsorcerer2747" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2921100); return false;" >TechSorcerer2747</a></span> <span class="odate time_1545263721 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Dec 2018 23:55</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4092706">
									

<p>The views and opinions within this entry do not reflect those of the author, and should not under any circumstances be subject to a Freudian interpretation about his relationship with his own mother.</p>
<p>I realize this is dense, lore-heavy, and probably steps on a lot of toes regarding people's headcanons, but I'm happy with how it turned out. A huge thank you to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/salamander724" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1486450); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1486450&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1545267491" alt="Salamander724" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1486450)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/salamander724" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1486450); return false;">Salamander724</a></span> from SCP-KO, without whom this would not have been possible, and to<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1404533); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1404533&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1545267491" alt="Zyn" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1404533)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1404533); return false;">Zyn</a></span>, who, as always, provides excellent feedback.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&quot;Hey,&nbsp;you're&nbsp;just&nbsp;trying&nbsp;to&nbsp;shoe-horn&nbsp;in&nbsp;a&nbsp;new&nbsp;GoI,&nbsp;aren't&nbsp;you?&quot;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Yes&nbsp;and&nbsp;No</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Uh, sort of. While the idea of the Children is something I'd love to expand upon, one that's been in my head for a while, this article and the idea of Name-based anomalies kind of hinges on them being the Children of the <em>Nameless</em> Queen. If it picks up traction, great. If not, I feel like there's a lot said about them here, and a lot of questions left to answer, which is fine by me.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

